    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Kirshenbaum Gets Wyndham Account</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By STUART ELLIOT</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Wyndham Hotels and Resorts names Kirshenbaum Bond &amp; Partners to handle its advertising account, with billings estimated at $35 million; account had been handled by Richards Group (Advertising column) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Wyndham Hotels and Resorts, part of Wyndham International, has named Kirshenbaum Bond &amp; Partners in New York to handle its account, with billings estimated at $35 million.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Wyndham Hotels and Resorts, part of Wyndham International, has named Kirshenbaum Bond &amp; Partners in New York to handle its account, with billings estimated at $35 million.</p>
        <p>The decision came after a two-month review, Andrew Jordan, senior vice president for marketing at Wyndham in Dallas, said yesterday. The review had been narrowed to Kirshenbaum Bond and the Playa del Rey, Calif., office of TBWA/ Chiat/Day, part of the TBWA Worldwide unit of the Omnicom Group. The account had been handled for more than a decade by the Richards Group in Dallas, which declined to take part in the review.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
